title: Top US Tech Stocks For November
text: Tech stocks have been the biggest winners of the COVID world, surging ever since markets bottomed in March, and leading the recovery. While there are signs that tech can continue to rally, there are bearish indicators.

title: FTC chairman warns of antitrust threat as Facebook braces for action
text: In a speech that could foreshadow antitrust action against Facebook, Federal Trade Commission Chairman Joe Simons warned Thursday that antitrust regulators should be concerned about dominant companies scooping up startups that are competitive threats. "A monopolist can squash a nascent competitor by buying it, not just by targeting it with anti-competitive actions," Simons said at an American Bar Association conference.

title: Facebook part of election misinformation issue: Nancy Pelosi
text: CNBC's Ylan Mui reports on the latest comments from Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi regarding Facebook and Big Tech.

title: UK's competition watchdog can continue its probe into Facebook's Giphy deal, tribunal rules
text: Facebook's acquisition of animated picture platform Giphy can be probed by the U.K.'s Competition and Markets Authority (CMA), a tribunal court ruled Friday.

title: Growing Free Cash Flow Could Boost Facebook Stock To $370
text: Facebook is still worth considerably more as its free cash flow gushes higher. FB stock is worth up to 35% more than current levels, and could hit $370 or beyond.

title: Watch these key buy levels in Facebook and Alphabet after sell-off, charts suggest
text: Morgan Stanley is betting on growth for Facebook and Alphabet in 2021. Bill Baruch of Blue Line Capital lays out levels that could signal a buying opportunity.
